verses.text_plain: Paul, an apostle of Jesus Christ by the will of God, to the saints which are at Ephesus, and to the faithful in Christ Jesus:
verses.verse_html: 1Paul, an apostle of Jesus Christ by the will of God, to the saints which are at Ephesus, and to the faithful in Christ Jesus:

verses.text_plain: Grace be to you, and peace, from God our Father, and from the Lord Jesus Christ.
verses.verse_html: 2Grace be to you, and peace, from God our Father, and from the Lord Jesus Christ.

verses.text_plain: Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who hath blessed us with all spiritual blessings in heavenly places in Christ:
verses.verse_html: 3Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who hath blessed us with all spiritual blessings in heavenly places in Christ:

verses.text_plain: According as he hath chosen us in him before the foundation of the world, that we should be holy and without blame before him in love:
verses.verse_html: 4According as he hath chosen us in him before the foundation of the world, that we should be holy and without blame before him in love:

verses.text_plain: Having predestinated us unto the adoption of children by Jesus Christ to himself, according to the good pleasure of his will,
verses.verse_html: 5Having predestinated us unto the adoption of children by Jesus Christ to himself, according to the good pleasure of his will,

verses.text_plain: To the praise of the glory of his grace, wherein he hath made us accepted in the beloved.
verses.verse_html: 6To the praise of the glory of his grace, wherein he hath made us accepted in the beloved.

verses.text_plain: In whom we have redemption through his blood, the forgiveness of sins, according to the riches of his grace;
verses.verse_html: 7In whom we have redemption through his blood, the forgiveness of sins, according to the riches of his grace;

verses.text_plain: Wherein he hath abounded toward us in all wisdom and prudence;
verses.verse_html: 8Wherein he hath abounded toward us in all wisdom and prudence;

verses.text_plain: Having made known unto us the mystery of his will, according to his good pleasure which he hath purposed in himself:
verses.verse_html: 9Having made known unto us the mystery of his will, according to his good pleasure which he hath purposed in himself:

verses.text_plain: That in the dispensation of the fulness of times he might gather together in one all things in Christ, both which are in heaven, and which are on earth; even in him:
verses.verse_html: 10That in the dispensation of the fulness of times he might gather together in one all things in Christ, both which are in heaven, and which are on earth; even in him:

tokens.text: he might gather together in one

verses.text_plain: In whom also we have obtained an inheritance, being predestinated according to the purpose of him who worketh all things after the counsel of his own will:
verses.verse_html: 11In whom also we have obtained an inheritance, being predestinated according to the purpose of him who worketh all things after the counsel of his own will:

verses.text_plain: That we should be to the praise of his glory, who first trusted in Christ.
verses.verse_html: 12That we should be to the praise of his glory, who first trusted in Christ.

verses.text_plain: In whom ye also trusted, after that ye heard the word of truth, the gospel of your salvation: in whom also after that ye believed, ye were sealed with that holy Spirit of promise,
verses.verse_html: 13In whom ye also trusted, after that ye heard the word of truth, the gospel of your salvation: in whom also after that ye believed, ye were sealed with that holy Spirit of promise,

verses.text_plain: Which is the earnest of our inheritance until the redemption of the purchased possession, unto the praise of his glory.
verses.verse_html: 14Which is the earnest of our inheritance until the redemption of the purchased possession, unto the praise of his glory.

verses.text_plain: Wherefore I also, after I heard of your faith in the Lord Jesus, and love unto all the saints,
verses.verse_html: 15Wherefore I also, after I heard of your faith in the Lord Jesus, and love unto all the saints,

verses.text_plain: Cease not to give thanks for you, making mention of you in my prayers;
verses.verse_html: 16Cease not to give thanks for you, making mention of you in my prayers;

verses.text_plain: That the God of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Father of glory, may give unto you the spirit of wisdom and revelation in the knowledge of him:
verses.verse_html: 17That the God of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Father of glory, may give unto you the spirit of wisdom and revelation in the knowledge of him:

verses.text_plain: The eyes of your understanding being enlightened; that ye may know what is the hope of his calling, and what the riches of the glory of his inheritance in the saints,
verses.verse_html: 18The eyes of your understanding being enlightened; that ye may know what is the hope of his calling, and what the riches of the glory of his inheritance in the saints,

verses.text_plain: And what is the exceeding greatness of his power to us-ward who believe, according to the working of his mighty power,
verses.verse_html: 19And what is the exceeding greatness of his power to us-ward who believe, according to the working of his mighty power,

verses.text_plain: Which he wrought in Christ, when he raised him from the dead, and set him at his own right hand in the heavenly places,
verses.verse_html: 20Which he wrought in Christ, when he raised him from the dead, and set him at his own right hand in the heavenly places,

verses.text_plain: Far above all principality, and power, and might, and dominion, and every name that is named, not only in this world, but also in that which is to come:
verses.verse_html: 21Far above all principality, and power, and might, and dominion, and every name that is named, not only in this world, but also in that which is to come:

verses.text_plain: And hath put all things under his feet, and gave him to be the head over all things to the church,
verses.verse_html: 22And hath put all things under his feet, and gave him to be the head over all things to the church,

verses.text_plain: Which is his body, the fulness of him that filleth all in all.
verses.verse_html: 23Which is his body, the fulness of him that filleth all in all.
